title: Importation of live birds and poultry meat from the Mainland suspended
content_text: Following announcement made by the Mainland that further suspected avian influenza outbreak had been found in the Guangdong Province, Anhui Province and Shanghai city, a spokesman for the Health, Welfare and Food Bureau said tonight (January 30) that the Government has temporarily suspended import of live birds and poultry meat from the Mainland. "We have received notification from the Mainland authorities on the outbreak situation and decided that all live birds, including chickens, ducks, geese, pet birds and day-old chickens, and all poultry meat would not be allowed to be exported to Hong Kong with immediate effect," the spokesman said.
